                  </persName>
            .</p>
               <p>WILLIAM SIMMONS. I am a <rs id="t18280911-386-viclabel2010" type="occupation">servant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-386-victim2080 t18280911-386-viclabel2010"></join>. On the 7th of of September I was in <placeName id="t18280911-386-crimeloc2011">St. James-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-386-crimeloc2011" type="placeName" value="St. James-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-386-crimeloc2011" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-386-off2008 t18280911-386-crimeloc2011"></join>. near the door of No. 50; my hat had been in the inner hall; I saw the prisoner come with it down the steps; he ran up the street; I pursued and took him with it in his hand - he said "Is this it."</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-386-person2081">
                  JAMES 
                  ADAMS
               <interp inst="t18280911-386-person2081" type="surname" value="ADAMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-386-person2081" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-386-person2081" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer - I took the prisoner and bring the hat.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. A person ran by me and dropped the hat, and when the prosecutor came up to me I told him so; on the way to the watch-house; he said, "I think I have made a mistake, and I wish to let him go," but I said"I will not be let go, I am given in charge, and let the officer do his duty." At the watch-house he had his doubts, but he was persuaded to press the charge.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182809110178"></xptr>WILLIAM SIMMONS. He never told me that a person had dropped the hat; I never expressed any doubt about his person and - I it would cause me a good deal of trouble had I not better let him go; but the watchman said"You have given him in charge and he must go:" he said he did not wish to be let go; he had a companion with him.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-386-person2082">
                  JAMES 
                  ADAMS
               <interp inst="t18280911-386-person2082" type="surname" value="ADAMS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-386-person2082" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-386-person2082" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I did not hear the prosecutor express a wish to let him go; he said it would cost him a great deal of trouble, might he not as well let him go; he never expressed any doubt about his person.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18280911-386-verdict2012" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18280911-386-verdict2012" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
